<!DOCTYPE recipe [<!ELEMENT recipe ((title?,details?,ingredients, instructions?,cuisine) | (title?,cuisine,details?,ingredients, instructions?))><!ELEMENT title (#PCDATA)><!ELEMENT cuisine (#PCDATA)><!ELEMENT ingredients (#PCDATA)><!ELEMENT instructions (#PCDATA)><!ELEMENT details (#PCDATA)>]>
<recipe>
<title>
Slow Cooker Beef Barbacoa
</title>
<details>
AUTHOR: I Heart Eating
PREP TIME: 15 minutes
COOK TIME: 11 hours
TOTAL TIME: 11 hours 15 minutes
COURSE: Main Course
CUISINE: American, Mexican
KEYWORD: beef, crock pot
SERVINGS: 10 servings
</details>
<ingredients>
1 tablespoon kosher salt
1 teaspoon dried crumbled rosemary
1 teaspoon ground black pepper
1 teaspoon ground coriander
1 teaspoon ancho chile powder
2 tablespoons olive oil
3-4 pound boneless beef chuck roast
3/4 cup water
2 bay leaves
3 cloves garlic minced
1 cup barbecue sauce
1 tablespoon hot sauce like Chipotle Tabasco Sauce
</ingredients>
<instructions>
In a small bowl, stir together salt, rosemary, pepper, coriander, and chile powder. 
Rub spice mixture on both sides of roast. Set aside.
Heat olive oil in a skillet over medium heat.
Add roast and brown on both sides. 
Place roast in slow cooker. 
Add water, bay leaves, and garlic to slow cooker. 
Cover, and cook on low for 10 hours or on high for 5 hours. 
Stir in barbecue sauce and hot sauce. 
Continue cooking for another hour on low. 
Shred beef in sauce. 
</instructions>
<cuisine>American, Mexican</cuisine></recipe>